radiographic_examinations.findings: Deposits at the disrupted ellipsoid zone, visual field test shows temporal hemianopia of the left eye.
Multiple serpiginous signal-void channels at the retrobulbar region of the left orbit with probable compression on the left ophthalmic nerve.

Total occlusion of the horizontal cavernous segment of the left internal carotid artery with collaterals; total occlusion of the terminal segment of the right internal carotid artery with prominent collaterals supplying bilateral anterior cerebral arteries.
Prominent collaterals around the optic canal compressing the optic nerve.
